&lt;h2 id=&#34;about-this-site&#34;&gt;About This Site
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;content&#34;&gt;Content
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Back when I was more of an artsy type, I enjoyed sharing bits of my personal life. These days, I focus on documenting my learning and work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-name-nullshow&#34;&gt;The Name: Nullshow
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;null&lt;/strong&gt; stands for â€œemptyâ€â€”a reflection of how I view life, and a reminder to always keep a beginnerâ€™s mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;show&lt;/strong&gt;  sounds like part of my Chinese name. The pronunciation of &lt;strong&gt;Nullshow&lt;/strong&gt; is close to a childhood nickname, which brings back memories of carefree days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;illustrations&#34;&gt;Illustrations
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;All &lt;strong&gt;category&lt;/strong&gt; illustrations come from Feng Zikai (1898â€“1975), a pioneer of Chinese comic art. His works are drawn from everyday lifeâ€”simple, expressive, and full of childlike charm. He was from the same hometown as me. Using his art is both a tribute and a reminder to stay mindful of the beauty in daily life, beyond study and work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;gratitude&#34;&gt;Gratitude
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;This site was built with inspiration and silent help from many brilliant minds online. Itâ€™s made me truly appreciate the power of open-source and sharing. In this era of technological revolution, AI is making everything simpler and faster. I hope Iâ€™m not just swept along by the tide &amp;ndash; but riding the wave with intention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thanks for joining me on this journey in such an exciting time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
